COD-EM description:
Armenia administrative level 0-1 edge-matched gazetteer, shapefiles, geodatabase, and geoservice.

These boundaries are suitable for database or GIS linkage to the [Armenia - Subnational Population Statistics](https://data.humdata.org/dataset/cod-ps-arm) tables using the ADM0, ADM1, and ADM2_PCODE fields.

COD-EM datasets do not replace the authoritative [COD-AB available here](https://data.humdata.org/dataset/cod-ab-arm); however COD-EM datasets may be preferred for cartographic purposes.  See caveats.

Vetting and live service provision by [Information Technology Outreach Services (ITOS)](https://www.uga.edu/) with funding from USAID.

"Ukraine administrative level 0-4 boundaries (COD-AB) dataset.

NOTE:  The population statistics common operatioanl dataset (COD-PS-UKR) is only available vis special request.  See [Ukraine - Subnational Population Statistics](https://data.humdata.org/dataset/cod-ps-ukr).  Users should use the 'Request Data' button.

This COD-AB was most recently reviewed for accuracy and necessary changes in April 2024.  The COD-AB does not require any update.

Sourced from State Scientific Production Enterprise “Kartographia”

Live geoservices are available for this COD-AB.  Please see [COD_External](https://codgis.itos.uga.edu/arcgis/rest/services/COD_External).  (For any earlier versions please see [here](https://codgis.itos.uga.edu/arcgis/rest/services/V00_0), [here](https://codgis.itos.uga.edu/arcgis/rest/services/V1_00), and [here](https://codgis.itos.uga.edu/arcgis/rest/services/V2_00).)  Vetting, configuration, and geoservices provision by Information Technology Outreach Services (ITOS) with funding from USAID.

This COD-AB is suitable for database or GIS linkage to the Ukraine [COD-PS](https://data.humdata.org/dataset/cod-ps-ukr).
An edge-matched (COD-EM) version of this COD-AB is available on [HDX here:](https://data.humdata.org/dataset/cod-em-ukr)
Please see the [COD Portal](https://cod.unocha.org/).

Administrative level 1 contains 27 feature(s).

Administrative level 2 contains 139 feature(s).

Administrative level 3 contains 1769 feature(s).

Administrative level 4 contains 29707 feature(s)."
